"settings":{"faq-ans":"<p>We're pleased to say that Counter Clean is pH neutral, which means it’s safe to use on most surfaces. That includes softer materials like aluminium, wood, stone, quartz and other sealed surfaces. We do recommend patch testing first on any particularly sensitive or precious surfaces you’re concerned about. Just spray onto a cloth and wipe a small patch to see the results. <\/p>"}},"3c474819-85aa-4a9a-bcc0-dc1e0f54550d":{"settings":{"faq-ans":"<p>We offer lots of subscription options, upgrade your subscription to more products, changing the frequency of your deliveries or cancelling your membership altogether. Subscriptions are set to a 90-day frequency by default, but you can always move your next billing date if you need to in a few easy steps. We understand there might be times when you need to stop your deliveries, and we’ll always respect your decision to leave - even if we’ll miss you. <\/p><p>If you have any trouble managing your subscription, our Customer Experience Team is always on hand to respond to your questions and requests as soon as possible. They’re very friendly.<\/p>"}},"text_VFatU":{"type":"text","disabled":false,"settings":{"open":false,"faq-question":"How many uses will I get out of a bottle?","faq-ans":"<p>A 300ml bottle of Counter Clean (including one 20ml concentrate) contains about 230 sprays. A typical household will get through one of our 300ml bottles in two to four weeks, unless you get a bit addicted to wiping down your surfaces like we have!<\/p>"}},"b3da5911-c83c-46b6-b545-797e91781fff":{"settings":{"faq-ans":"<p>We aim for all orders to be dispatched within one working day, and for you to receive it within 3-5 calendar days.<br\/><br\/>If you have questions about delivery, please reach out to us and a member of our Customer Experience team will get back to you as soon as possible.<\/p>"}},"29134be3-da11-47cf-a53b-7f88d2bbe596":{"settings":{"faq-ans":"<p>Our products are safe to use around dogs and other domestic pets, but if you’re worried about allergies it’s always best to check with your vet. Birds are particularly sensitive to airborne substances so it’s a good idea to take them out of the room while you clean. <\/p><p>It’s also important to note that Ylang Ylang and Citronella are both toxic to dogs if they’re ingested or applied topically, so naturally we wouldn’t recommend that. It probably goes without saying, but please don’t let your pets lick or drink Counter Clean or Bathroom Bliss.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["d5f0750c-d1c1-4e82-bde9-e538cec56d97","3bef21b1-6cdf-4174-a35c-01e4fa513c76","text_gwXQrP","3c474819-85aa-4a9a-bcc0-dc1e0f54550d","text_VFatU","b3da5911-c83c-46b6-b545-797e91781fff","29134be3-da11-47cf-a53b-7f88d2bbe596"]},"1616c4c5-6d10-4f48-a274-122128027936":{"custom_css":[".common-btn-width {width: 343px;}",".social-video-wrapper video {border-radius: 4px;}",".blue-starterkit-btn {font-size: 16px;}",".social-videos-slider .slick-dots {background: #e7ebea;}","@media (max-width: 768px) {.video-block-wrapper {padding-block: 32px; } .common-btn-width {width: 100%; } .video-block-wrapper .heading-2 {font-size: 32px !important; }}"],"settings":{"top":"0"},"blocks":{}}},"order":["announcement_bar_reskin_8YjFiD","banner_10_zHYgWz","icon_odl_Yqqgc","marquee_block_reskin_KfyWkz","icon_blocks_reskin_cUrCPd","toggle_image_block_dayYyU","blocks_reskin_UTLzLD","blocks_reskin_385_P8w8J","single_buy_box_mk7g83","two_women_385_6pgrm","4f5b5391-b1ab-4116-9ae8-7c2e152c9c8d","0d7b4809-b3f0-4552-b395-2a0fcac97820","a2194449-184e-4118-8225-9a59caeea728","1616c4c5-6d10-4f48-a274-122128027936","footer_3_m9QXhQ","footer_2_Vy9DjJ","complete_starterkit_js_VfKmFr"]}